140.     The initial loan was made by several bank insiders with an interest in this land deal steered the loan to the bank.  (See generally, Burge, 2/15/96 Dep., pp. 22-26). The original Whitewater loan for $182,611 was brought to the Flippin Bank by Chris Wade, a director of Flippin Bank and the local realtor who sold the property, and ushered through with the assistance of James Patterson, President and director of Flippin Bank  and a shareholder in 101 River Development, Inc., the owners of a larger parcel of land that included the Whitewater property. (Burge, 2/15/96 Dep. p. 21).  <BR>

