<br><h3>SURVEY: <a href="http://www.economist.com/surveys/banking/">BANKING</a></h3>
<ul>Fears about systemic risk in banking have led to calls for ever more rules and regulations. But would they be part of the solution or part of the problem? Martin Giles reports</ul>
</td></tr></table><br><p align=center><a href="http://www.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Page</a> &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/cgi-bin/search_form.cgi?830559600,iss">Search</a> &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/mailing/">Summaries by e-mail</a></p>

