<hr size=6 align=center width=65%>
<center><table width=65%><tr valign=top><td valign=top width=30%>

<p><b>Beggar off</b> &nbsp; Tony Blair, the Labour Party leader, was criticised for endorsing strict measures to keep beggars and homeless people off the streets in an interview with the <i>Big Issue</i>, a magazine sold by the homeless. He also refused to support a scheme to allow the homeless to register to vote at daycare centres.<br>
<p><b>Lib-Lab love-in</b> &nbsp; Labour and the Liberal Democrats came close to agreement in talks on constitutional reform. But Mr Blair would not commit himself to changes to the electoral system proposed by the Lib Dems, and Liz Lynne, a Liberal Democrat <font size=-1>MP</font>, attacked the proposed pact.<br>
<p><b>Teaching a lesson</b> &nbsp; The National Association of Head Teachers asked its members to boycott training programmes for student teachers unless the government called off its planned reform of teachers' pensions.<br>
<p><b>Remarkable</b> &nbsp; An inquiry into the marking of last year's English <font size=-1>A</font>-levels by the Oxford and Cambridge Schools Examination Board found that pupils at some private schools were given higher grades than they deserved.<br>
</td><td width=5%></td><td valign=top width=30%>
<p><b>Giveaway</b> &nbsp; The Woolwich, Britain's third-largest building society, pledged to give each of its 2.5m eligible members a minimum of 450 free shares, estimated to be worth about &#163;900, when it becomes a bank in July.<br>
<p><b>Theatrics</b> &nbsp; The English National Opera announced a bid to build a new theatre with &#163;90m of funding from the National Lottery, just five years after the government paid &#163;10.5m to buy the freehold of the Coliseum, its current home. Scarborough council voted to provide extra funding to a theatre run by Sir Alan Ayckbourn, a playwright.<br>
<p><b>Deflated</b> &nbsp; Richard Branson, a business tycoon, was forced to abandon his attempt to circle the globe by balloon a mere 400 miles into the flight.<br>
<p><b>Sick pleasures</b> &nbsp; Academics at Plymouth University are conducting research into people who think they have benefited from falling ill.<br>

</td></tr></table></center>

